New World Resources Says Quarterly Coke, Coal Prices Rise

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-04-11T06:32:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/new-world-resources-says-quarterly-coke-coal-prices-rise-1-.html
New World Resources NV (NWR) , the largest
Czech producer of coal used by steelmakers, said contract prices
for coke and coal delivery in the second quarter rose.  The company agreed to deliver coking coal for an average
price of 215 euros ($310) per a ton, a rise of 35 percent from
the previous quarter, the miner said in a statement today. Coke
prices rose 19 percent from the previous quarter to 400 euros
per a ton, it said.  NWR said it is “on track” to fulfill its 2011 production
and sales targets. The miner will start selling all its coking
coal production on quarterly basis as of this month, it said in
the statement.  Thermal coal price for 2011 remained unchanged at 71 euros
a ton, a 13 percent increase on the 2010 average price, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story: 
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  